March 14 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media on Friday:

* European buyout firm Charterhouse Capital Partners LLP [CHCAP.UL] is nearing a deal to acquire education software provider Skillsoft Ltd [SSIPOK.UL] for more than $2 billion, people familiar with the matter said on Thursday. [ID:nL2N0MA2A3]  * Barclays <BARC.L> is reviewing the size and shape of its investment bank, in a review that is expected to result in it shrinking and focusing on its most profitable areas, two people familiar with the matter said on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0MA4LZ]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]